    <summaries>
      <summary>
        <versionCode>00</versionCode>
        <actionDate>2020-03-19</actionDate>
        <actionDesc>Introduced in Senate</actionDesc>
        <updateDate>2020-06-12T13:37:01Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p><b>Reward Work Act </b></p> <p>This bill revises provisions related to stock buybacks. </p> <p>An issuer of securities may not purchase its own securities on a national exchange if the issuer has (1) received specified financial assistance related to the COVID-19 (i.e., coronavirus disease 2019) pandemic, and (2) repurchased more than $1 billion worth of its own securities in the last five years. Additionally, one-third of such issuer's&nbsp;board of directors&nbsp;must be&nbsp;elected by employees for the issuer to be allowed&nbsp;to register securities. </p> <p>The bill also repeals the Securities and Exchange Commission regulation (Rule 10b-18) that generally provides a safe harbor from market manipulation liability for an issuer engaging in a stock buyback. </p>]]></text>
      </summary>
